issues.description:
**As a** frontend developer, **I want** the topic rendering logic extracted from `VectorTopicMemory.tsx` into a shared `TopicList` component, **so that** both `VectorTopicMemory` and `FeedbackAnalysis` can render memory topics without duplicating code.

## Background

`VectorTopicMemory.tsx` contains a `TopicCard` function component and topic list rendering logic that displays memory tiers (hot/warm/cold badges), lifecycle tiers (new/trending/established), keywords, exemplars, member counts, and days inactive. This rendering is currently tightly coupled to the VectorTopicMemory block.

FeedbackAnalysis needs to render the same topic cards in its memories section. Rather than duplicating the rendering code, extract it into a reusable component.

## Solution

Create `dashboard/components/ui/topic-list.tsx` containing:

- `TopicCard` component — renders a single topic with all its metadata badges, keywords, and exemplars
- `TopicList` component — renders a list of `TopicCard` items, optionally grouped by score

Props interface:

```typescript
interface TopicItem {
  cluster_id: number;
  label: string;
  keywords?: string[];
  exemplars?: Array<string | { text: string; item_id?: string; identifiers?: Record<string, string> }>;
  memory_weight: number;
  memory_tier: string;
  lifecycle_tier?: string;
  is_new?: boolean;
  is_trending?: boolean;
  member_count: number;
  p95_distance?: number;
  days_inactive?: number;
  has_short_term_memory?: boolean;
  has_medium_term_memory?: boolean;
  has_long_term_memory?: boolean;
}

interface TopicListProps {
  topics: TopicItem[];
  title?: string;
  collapsible?: boolean;
  defaultExpanded?: boolean;
}
```

The `exemplars` type is a union to support both the old format (plain strings from existing VectorTopicMemory output) and the new format (objects with item_id and identifiers from Story plx-679a29).

After extraction, `VectorTopicMemory.tsx` imports and uses the shared component instead of its inline rendering.

## Key Files

- Create: `dashboard/components/ui/topic-list.tsx`
- Modify: `dashboard/components/blocks/VectorTopicMemory.tsx` — replace inline rendering with shared component

## Dependencies

None. Can start in parallel with backend stories.

## Missing Release of Resource after Effective Lifetime

**Severity:** medium
**Package:** inflight@1.0.6
**File:** `dashboard/package.json`

**CVSS Score:** 6.2  
**Exploit Maturity:** proof-of-concept  
**Snyk Priority Score:** 417/1000

### CVEs
No CVE assigned.

**Fix:** No automatic fix available. Review manually.

### Details
## Overview

Affected versions of this package are vulnerable to Missing Release of Resource after Effective Lifetime via the `makeres` function due to improperly deleting keys from the `reqs` object after execution of callbacks. This behavior causes the keys to remain in the `reqs` object, which leads to resource exhaustion.

Exploiting this vulnerability results in crashing the `node` process or in the application crash.

**Note:**
This library is not maintained, and currently, there is no fix for this issue. To overcome this vulnerability, several dependent packages have eliminated the use of this library.

To trigger the memory leak, an attacker would need to have the ability to execute or influence the asynchronous operations that use the inflight module within the application. This typically requires access to the internal workings of the server or application, which is not commonly exposed to remote users. Therefore, “Attack vector” is marked as “Local”.
## PoC
```js
const inflight = require('inflight');

function testInflight() {
  let i = 0;
  function scheduleNext() {
    let key = `key-${i++}`;
    const callback = () => {
    };
    for (let j = 0; j < 1000000; j++) {
      inflight(key, callback);
    }

    setImmediate(scheduleNext);
  }


  if (i % 100 === 0) {
    console.log(process.memoryUsage());
  }

  scheduleNext();
}

testInflight();
```
## Remediation
There is no fixed version for `inflight`.
## References
- [GitHub Issue](https://github.com/isaacs/inflight/issues/5)
- [GitHub PR](https://github.com/logdna/logdna-agent/pull/157)


### Reference
- [Snyk advisory](https://security.snyk.io/vuln/SNYK-JS-INFLIGHT-6095116)

**As a** report consumer, **I want** the FeedbackAnalysis block to render a collapsible "Topic Memories" section below the confusion matrix detail, **so that** I can see clustered feedback patterns in context with the agreement metrics.

## Background

With Story plx-3d5cea, the FeedbackAnalysis backend now produces a `memories` key in its output containing per-score topic lists with enriched exemplars. With Story plx-17451f, a shared `TopicList` component exists to render topics with keywords, memory tiers, lifecycle flags, and exemplars. With Story plx-7826af, exemplars render with `IdentifierDisplay` Item links. This story wires all the pieces together in the FeedbackAnalysis frontend.

The FeedbackAnalysis rendering chain is: `FeedbackAnalysis.tsx` -> `FeedbackAnalysisDisplay` -> `ScorecardReport`. The memories section is added in `FeedbackAnalysis.tsx`, rendered below the `FeedbackAnalysisDisplay` component. In single-scorecard mode, it appears directly after the analysis display. In all-scorecards mode, it appears inside each expanded scorecard's detail view.

## Solution

1. In `FeedbackAnalysis.tsx`, after the `<FeedbackAnalysisDisplay>` component, check if `feedbackData.memories` exists and has content
2. If present, render a collapsible section with header "Topic Memories" using the same expand/collapse pattern (ChevronUp/ChevronDown) used elsewhere in the component
3. Inside the collapsible, render `<TopicList>` (from Story plx-17451f) for each score's topics
4. The section is collapsed by default — the agreement metrics remain the primary content
5. In all-scorecards mode, the memories section appears within each scorecard's expanded detail, after the `FeedbackAnalysisDisplay`

## Data Shape

The `memories` key in `feedbackData` has this structure:

```typescript
memories?: {
  scores: Array<{
    score_name: string;
    score_id: string;
    topics: Array<{
      topic_id: number;
      label: string;
      keywords: string[];
      exemplars: Array<{
        text: string;
        item_id?: string;
        identifiers?: Record<string, string>;
      }>;
      member_count: number;
      memory_weight: number;
      memory_tier: "hot" | "warm" | "cold";
      lifecycle_tier: "new" | "trending" | "established";
      is_new: boolean;
      is_trending: boolean;
    }>;
  }>;
}
```

## Key Files

- Modify: `dashboard/components/blocks/FeedbackAnalysis.tsx` — add memories section in both single and all-scorecards modes
- Import: shared `TopicList` component from `dashboard/components/ui/topic-list.tsx` (Story plx-17451f)
- Type: extend `FeedbackAnalysisData` interface with optional `memories` field

## Dependencies

- Story plx-3d5cea (FeedbackAnalysis runs memory analysis — backend data)
- Story plx-17451f (Extract shared TopicList component — rendering)
- Story plx-7826af (Exemplars render with IdentifierDisplay — Item links)
